I should probably preface this one by admitting that I think Ricky Gervais is funny.
A weirdly divisive statement to make these days, and one I am about to caveat thoroughly, but I think that any review of Gervais’s work – and it is impossible to take Ricky Gervais (the concept) out of any show featuring Ricky Gervais (actor, writer, creator) – needs to state where you are, on him, as a person.
I liked The Office in a way that eclipsed part of my personality for ever.
After Life continues along those well-worn lines, in a way that says: “This is what Ricky Gervais does now.
But for the legion of new-money Gervais fans who I absolutely don’t and never will understand, here you go.